	<http://tesserai.io/ontology/created_at> "2026-03-26T14:50:48.627709+00:00" ;
	<http://tesserai.io/ontology/content> "`briefing.md` is written at `/private/tmp/swarm-final-news/briefing.md`. Here's what it covers:\n\n**Structure:**\n- **Executive Summary** — 3 paragraphs for a senior audience: Omnibus vote, lobbying tensions, enforcement actions\n- **6 Key Developments** with specific dates, named actors, and figures:\n  1. Digital Omnibus plenary vote (March 26, 2026) — institutional comparison table, trilogue preview\n  2. Corporate Europe Observatory lobbying analysis — 7-of-8 match, specific legal provisions\n  3. Meta's confrontational posture — GPAI refusal, WhatsApp antitrust, far-right MEP lobbying (1→38 meetings)\n  4. US trade pressure — Greer naming SAP/Spotify/Mistral, 25% tariff threat, March 20 AI strategy\n  5. Parliament copyright resolution (March 10, 2026) — 460–71 vote, EUIPO opt-out register\n  6. X/Grok enforcement action (January 8, 2026) — first GPAI data retention order\n- **Outlook** — immediate (weeks), medium-term (months), and structural trend analysis\n- **8 sources** with full URLs where available\n\nNo information was fabricated — all facts, figures, quotes, and dates come directly from the prior research findings." ;
	<http://tesserai.io/ontology/confidence> "0.8"^^<http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#double> ;
	<http://tesserai.io/ontology/agent_id> "87048f0b-0c28-4e2b-bdce-85dca2476633" ;
	<http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "`briefing.md` is written at `/private/tmp/swarm-final-news/briefing.md`. Here's what it covers:\n\n**Structure:**\n- **Executive Summary** — 3 paragraphs for a senior audience: Omnibus vote, lobbying tensions, enforcement actions\n- **6 Key Developments** with specific dates, named actors, and figures:\n  1. Digital Omnibus plenary vote (March 26, 2026) — institutional comparison table, trilogue preview\n  2. Corporate Europe Observatory lobbying analysis — 7-of-8 match, specific legal provisions\n  3. Meta's confrontational posture — GPAI refusal, WhatsApp antitrust, far-right MEP lobbying (1→38 meetings)\n  4. US trade pressure — Greer naming SAP/Spotify/Mistral, 25% tariff threat, March 20 AI strategy\n  5. Parliament copyright resolution (March 10, 2026) — 460–71 vote, EUIPO opt-out register\n  6. X/Grok enforcement action (January 8, 2026) — first GPAI data retention order\n- **Outlook** — immediate (weeks), medium-term (months), and structural trend analysis\n- **8 sources** with full URLs where available\n\nNo information was fabricated — all facts, figures, quotes, and dates come directly from the prior research findings." ;
