# === memory-490192ae-107f-459d-b98c-aa69ec1103f6 ===
<urn:tesserai:twin:memory-490192ae-107f-459d-b98c-aa69ec1103f6> <http://tesserai.io/ontology/createdAt> "2026-03-26T14:36:20.234817Z"^^<http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime> ;
	<http://tesserai.io/ontology/topics> "[\"Research EU AI Act enforcement and implementation\",\"Deep-read top enforcement articles\",\"researcher\"]" ;
	<http://tesserai.io/ontology/tool_name> "researcher" ;
	<http://tesserai.io/ontology/structured_data> "null" ;
	<http://tesserai.io/ontology/run_id> "509d6c4d-899c-4d0a-9f3c-4b808bd83541" ;
	<http://tesserai.io/ontology/memory_type> "episodic" ;
	<http://tesserai.io/ontology/created_at> "2026-03-26T14:36:20.234154+00:00" ;
	<http://tesserai.io/ontology/content> "I need permission to write the file. Please approve the write to `/private/tmp/swarm-final-news/research-enforcement.md`.\n\nIn the meantime, here's a summary of what the deep-read found:\n\n---\n\n## Key Enriched Findings\n\n### X / Grok (Jan 8, 2026)\n- Commission issued a **data retention order** targeting Grok's \"Spicy Mode\" — alleged generation of non-consensual sexualized imagery and potential CSAM\n- Legal basis: AI Act safety requirements + DSA illegal content provisions\n- Potential penalty: up to **6% of global annual turnover** under DSA\n\n### Meta / WhatsApp (Jan–Feb 9, 2026)\n- Commission opened **antitrust investigation** after Meta blocked rival AIs (OpenAI, Perplexity) from WhatsApp Business API while allowing Meta's own AI\n- **February 9, 2026**: Commission notified Meta of intent to impose **interim measures** (a rare emergency tool)\n- Meta responded by allowing third-party AIs on WhatsApp — subject to a fee; whether that satisfies the EU is unresolved\n\n### Digital Omnibus (Mar 18, 2026 — IMCO/LIBE vote)\n- Vote: **101 in favour, 9 against, 8 abstentions**\n- Annex III delayed to **Dec 2, 2027**; Article 50§2 watermarking tightened to **Nov 2, 2026** (Parliament shortened Commission's proposed grace period)\n- Parliament added a new **\"nudifier\" ban** (AI systems generating non-consensual sexualized imagery) to Article 5 prohibited practices\n- Plenary vote expected today (Mar 26); then trilogue with Council — **August 2, 2026 still legally binding until final adoption**\n\n### Implementation gaps\n- Only **8 of 27 member states** have designated enforcement contacts — 7 months past deadline\n- Commission missed its own guidance deadlines; harmonized standards now targeting **end of 2026**\n- Finland is the most advanced (full implementation complete Dec 2025)\n\nSources:\n- [Financial Content/WRAL — X and Meta enforcement](https://markets.financialcontent.com/wral/article/tokenring-2026-1-9-the-brussels-effect-in-action-eu-ai-act-enforcement-targets-x-and-meta-as-global-standards-solidify)\n- [CNBC — EU interim measures Meta](https://www.cnbc.com/2026/02/09/eu-interim-measures-meta-whatsapp-ai-policy-antritrust.html)\n- [aiacto.eu — IMCO/LIBE vote Mar 18](https://www.aiacto.eu/en/blog/vote-imco-libe-digital-omnibus-ai-act-18-mars-2026)\n- [World Reporter — 8 of 27 states ready](https://worldreporter.com/eu-ai-act-august-2026-deadline-only-8-of-27-eu-states-ready-what-it-means-for-global-ai-compliance/)\n- [IAPP — Commission misses guidance deadline](https://iapp.org/news/a/european-commission-misses-deadline-for-ai-act-guidance-on-high-risk-systems)" ;
	<http://tesserai.io/ontology/confidence> "1"^^<http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#double> ;
	<http://tesserai.io/ontology/agent_id> "83a7567f-7a26-4472-9dee-527cc32e536f" ;
	<http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "I need permission to write the file. Please approve the write to `/private/tmp/swarm-final-news/research-enforcement.md`.\n\nIn the meantime, here's a summary of what the deep-read found:\n\n---\n\n## Key Enriched Findings\n\n### X / Grok (Jan 8, 2026)\n- Commission issued a **data retention order** targeting Grok's \"Spicy Mode\" — alleged generation of non-consensual sexualized imagery and potential CSAM\n- Legal basis: AI Act safety requirements + DSA illegal content provisions\n- Potential penalty: up to **6% of global annual turnover** under DSA\n\n### Meta / WhatsApp (Jan–Feb 9, 2026)\n- Commission opened **antitrust investigation** after Meta blocked rival AIs (OpenAI, Perplexity) from WhatsApp Business API while allowing Meta's own AI\n- **February 9, 2026**: Commission notified Meta of intent to impose **interim measures** (a rare emergency tool)\n- Meta responded by allowing third-party AIs on WhatsApp — subject to a fee; whether that satisfies the EU is unresolved\n\n### Digital Omnibus (Mar 18, 2026 — IMCO/LIBE vote)\n- Vote: **101 in favour, 9 against, 8 abstentions**\n- Annex III delayed to **Dec 2, 2027**; Article 50§2 watermarking tightened to **Nov 2, 2026** (Parliament shortened Commission's proposed grace period)\n- Parliament added a new **\"nudifier\" ban** (AI systems generating non-consensual sexualized imagery) to Article 5 prohibited practices\n- Plenary vote expected today (Mar 26); then trilogue with Council — **August 2, 2026 still legally binding until final adoption**\n\n### Implementation gaps\n- Only **8 of 27 member states** have designated enforcement contacts — 7 months past deadline\n- Commission missed its own guidance deadlines; harmonized standards now targeting **end of 2026**\n- Finland is the most advanced (full implementation complete Dec 2025)\n\nSources:\n- [Financial Content/WRAL — X and Meta enforcement](https://markets.financialcontent.com/wral/article/tokenring-2026-1-9-the-brussels-effect-in-action-eu-ai-act-enforcement-targets-x-and-meta-as-global-standards-solidify)\n- [CNBC — EU interim measures Meta](https://www.cnbc.com/2026/02/09/eu-interim-measures-meta-whatsapp-ai-policy-antritrust.html)\n- [aiacto.eu — IMCO/LIBE vote Mar 18](https://www.aiacto.eu/en/blog/vote-imco-libe-digital-omnibus-ai-act-18-mars-2026)\n- [World Reporter — 8 of 27 states ready](https://worldreporter.com/eu-ai-act-august-2026-deadline-only-8-of-27-eu-states-ready-what-it-means-for-global-ai-compliance/)\n- [IAPP — Commission misses guidance deadline](https://iapp.org/news/a/european-commission-misses-deadline-for-ai-act-guidance-on-high-risk-systems)" ;
	<http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "[researcher] I need permission to write the file. Please approve the write to `/private/tmp/s" ;
