# === memory-7649dc0f-46e7-4213-b898-9fa6916ce7cf ===
<urn:tesserai:twin:memory-7649dc0f-46e7-4213-b898-9fa6916ce7cf> <http://tesserai.io/ontology/createdAt> "2026-03-26T14:33:42.807823Z"^^<http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime> ;
	<http://tesserai.io/ontology/topics> "[\"Research EU AI Act enforcement and implementation\",\"Search for EU AI Act enforcement news\",\"researcher\"]" ;
	<http://tesserai.io/ontology/tool_name> "researcher" ;
	<http://tesserai.io/ontology/structured_data> "null" ;
	<http://tesserai.io/ontology/run_id> "509d6c4d-899c-4d0a-9f3c-4b808bd83541" ;
	<http://tesserai.io/ontology/memory_type> "episodic" ;
	<http://tesserai.io/ontology/created_at> "2026-03-26T14:33:42.807201+00:00" ;
	<http://tesserai.io/ontology/content> "The write tools require your approval. Please approve the file write request (to `/private/tmp/swarm-final-news/research-enforcement.md`) so I can save the research findings. Alternatively, if you'd like, I can share the full findings here in the chat.\n\nHere's a summary of what was gathered:\n\n---\n\n## EU AI Act Enforcement Research — Feb/Mar 2026 Findings\n\n### Critical deadline: 2 August 2026\nMost EU AI Act obligations become enforceable on this date, including Annex III high-risk AI (employment, credit, education, biometrics), Article 50 transparency rules, and full GPAI enforcement. Penalties reach €35M or 7% of global turnover.\n\n### Digital Omnibus — proposed delay moving fast (Mar 2026)\n- **13 Mar 2026**: EU Council adopted general approach\n- **18 Mar 2026**: EP IMCO+LIBE committees adopted joint negotiating position\n- **26 Mar 2026**: EP plenary vote expected (today)\n- If passed: Annex III deadline shifts to **2 Dec 2027**; Annex I to **2 Aug 2028**\n- Source: [EU Council press release](https://www.consilium.europa.eu/en/press/press-releases/2026/03/13/council-agrees-position-to-streamline-rules-on-artificial-intelligence/)\n\n### Active enforcement actions\n- **8 Jan 2026**: Commission issued data retention order to **X** over its Grok AI chatbot data\n- **Jan–Feb 2026**: Commission investigating **Meta/WhatsApp** for restricting rival AI providers; interim measures notified in February\n- Source: [Financial Content/WRAL](https://markets.financialcontent.com/wral/article/tokenring-2026-1-9-the-brussels-effect-in-action-eu-ai-act-enforcement-targets-x-and-meta-as-global-standards-solidify)\n\n### Prohibited practices (in force since Aug 2025)\n- **2 Feb 2026**: 1-year anniversary triggered mandatory Article 112 Commission review\n- No public enforcement actions announced yet, but investigations reportedly underway into emotion recognition, predictive policing, and social scoring systems\n- Source: [Quinn Emanuel](https://www.quinnemanuel.com/the-firm/publications/initial-prohibitions-under-eu-ai-act-take-effect/)\n\n### Transparency Code of Practice (AI-generated content)\n- **3 Mar 2026**: Second draft published, operationalizing Article 50\n- **30 Mar 2026**: Stakeholder feedback deadline\n- **Jun 2026**: Final version expected\n- Source: [Herbert Smith Freehills Kramer](https://www.hsfkramer.com/notes/ip/2026-03/transparency-obligations-for-ai-generated-content-under-the-eu-ai-act-from-principle-to-practice)\n\n### Member state readiness gap\nOnly **8 of 27 EU states** have designated national competent authorities — a major implementation risk ahead of August 2026.\n\n### Other March 2026 developments\n- **18 Mar 2026**: EP Think Tank published enforcement architecture analysis — [Epthinktank](https://epthinktank.eu/2026/03/18/enforcement-of-the-ai-act/)\n- **20 Mar 2026**: Seventh EU AI Board meeting held" ;
	<http://tesserai.io/ontology/confidence> "1"^^<http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#double> ;
	<http://tesserai.io/ontology/agent_id> "1b2b0e87-146d-4d2e-8d1b-5360e93600cc" ;
