# === memory-c2c5d11e-bb7c-43ac-9dd8-177d48b96939 ===
<urn:tesserai:twin:memory-c2c5d11e-bb7c-43ac-9dd8-177d48b96939> <http://tesserai.io/ontology/createdAt> "2026-03-26T14:38:50.709467Z"^^<http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime> ;
	<http://tesserai.io/ontology/topics> "[\"Research EU AI policy debates and new proposals\",\"Search for EU AI policy and legislative news\",\"researcher\"]" ;
	<http://tesserai.io/ontology/tool_name> "researcher" ;
	<http://tesserai.io/ontology/structured_data> "null" ;
	<http://tesserai.io/ontology/run_id> "509d6c4d-899c-4d0a-9f3c-4b808bd83541" ;
	<http://tesserai.io/ontology/memory_type> "episodic" ;
	<http://tesserai.io/ontology/created_at> "2026-03-26T14:38:50.708662+00:00" ;
	<http://tesserai.io/ontology/content> "The file write requires your approval. Please approve the write to `/private/tmp/swarm-final-news/research-policy.md`.\n\nIn the meantime, here is the full research summary:\n\n---\n\n## EU AI Policy Research — Feb/Mar 2026 Findings\n\n### 1. Digital Omnibus on AI (Main Legislative Event)\nThe dominant story. The Commission's Nov 2025 proposal is moving fast:\n- **13 Mar**: Council adopted its position\n- **18 Mar**: IMCO+LIBE committees voted 101-9-8 in favour\n- **26 Mar** (today): EP plenary vote scheduled; then trilogue\n\nParliament's key additions vs. Commission:\n- Fixed date: Annex III high-risk deadline → **2 Dec 2027**\n- Watermarking (Art. 50§2) tightened to **2 Nov 2026**\n- **New ban on \"nudifier\" AI** added to Article 5 prohibited practices\n- SME exemptions extended to \"small mid-caps\"\n- Reinforced AI Office powers over GPAI\n\n### 2. Copyright Resolution (10 Mar 2026)\nEP voted **460-71** for a non-binding resolution calling for:\n- EUIPO register of copyrighted works used in AI training\n- Fair remuneration for creators (creative sector = 6.9% of EU GDP)\n- Opt-out rights for rightsholders\n- No copyright protection for purely AI-generated content\n- EU law to apply regardless of where AI was trained\n\n### 3. AI-Generated Content Code of Practice\nCommission published **second draft on 5 Mar 2026** — simplified and more flexible than first draft.\n\n### 4. AI Liability Directive — Withdrawn\nThe dedicated AILD was formally withdrawn Feb 2025. The **Product Liability Directive** (member states must transpose by **Dec 2026**) is now the primary legal mechanism for AI-related harm claims.\n\n### 5. Sectoral AI (Healthcare/Finance)\n- Medical AI: obligations apply Aug 2026; devices embedded in MDR/IVDR products get extension to Aug 2027\n- Finance: credit scoring classified as high-risk; full obligations Aug 2026\n- All member states need at least one **AI regulatory sandbox** operational by Aug 2026\n\n### 6. Apply AI Strategy & Competitiveness Push\n19 AI Factories underway across 16 member states; majority operational by end of 2026. Q2 2026 actions include calls for AI model sharing across Digital Innovation Hubs. The Apply AI Alliance coordinates industry/academia input.\n\n### 7. GPAI Implementing Act\nCommission consulting on draft enforcement rules for GPAI providers — specifying information requests, model recalls, and fines. GPAI enforcement begins Aug 2026.\n\n---\n\nSources:\n- [EU Council — Digital Omnibus (13 Mar 2026)](https://www.consilium.europa.eu/en/press/press-releases/2026/03/13/council-agrees-position-to-streamline-rules-on-artificial-intelligence/)\n- [EP — nudification ban vote](https://www.europarl.europa.eu/news/en/agenda/plenary-news/2026-03-25/2/artificial-intelligence-parliament-to-vote-on-nudification-ban)\n- [EP plenary March II 2026](https://epthinktank.eu/2026/03/24/european-parliament-plenary-session-march-ii-2026/)\n- [IAPP — MEPs reach preliminary agreement on AI omnibus](https://iapp.org/news/a/meps-reach-preliminary-political-agreement-on-AI-omnibus)\n- [CDT Europe AI Bulletin March 2026](https://cdt.org/insights/cdt-europes-ai-bulletin-march-2026/)\n- [Euronews — copyright resolution (10 Mar 2026)](https://www.euronews.com/next/2026/03/10/eu-parliament-urges-new-rules-to-protect-creative-works-from-ai-training)\n- [EP — copyright text adopted (TA-10-2026-0066)](https://www.europarl.europa.eu/doceo/document/TA-10-2026-0066_EN.html)\n- [IAPP — AI Liability Directive withdrawn](https://iapp.org/news/a/european-commission-withdraws-ai-liability-directive-from-consideration)\n- [The Regulatory Review — paradoxes of EU AI regulation (10 Mar 2026)](https://www.theregreview.org/2026/03/10/rangone-the-paradoxes-of-the-european-unions-ai-regulation/)\n- [EU Commission — Apply AI Strategy](https://digital-strategy.ec.europa.eu/en/policies/apply-ai)" ;
	<http://tesserai.io/ontology/confidence> "1"^^<http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#double> ;
	<http://tesserai.io/ontology/agent_id> "83ebd778-c3af-4027-96c5-a0293d8b0a06" ;
	<http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "The file write requires your approval. Please approve the write to `/private/tmp/swarm-final-news/research-policy.md`.\n\nIn the meantime, here is the full research summary:\n\n---\n\n## EU AI Policy Research — Feb/Mar 2026 Findings\n\n### 1. Digital Omnibus on AI (Main Legislative Event)\nThe dominant story. The Commission's Nov 2025 proposal is moving fast:\n- **13 Mar**: Council adopted its position\n- **18 Mar**: IMCO+LIBE committees voted 101-9-8 in favour\n- **26 Mar** (today): EP plenary vote scheduled; then trilogue\n\nParliament's key additions vs. Commission:\n- Fixed date: Annex III high-risk deadline → **2 Dec 2027**\n- Watermarking (Art. 50§2) tightened to **2 Nov 2026**\n- **New ban on \"nudifier\" AI** added to Article 5 prohibited practices\n- SME exemptions extended to \"small mid-caps\"\n- Reinforced AI Office powers over GPAI\n\n### 2. Copyright Resolution (10 Mar 2026)\nEP voted **460-71** for a non-binding resolution calling for:\n- EUIPO register of copyrighted works used in AI training\n- Fair remuneration for creators (creative sector = 6.9% of EU GDP)\n- Opt-out rights for rightsholders\n- No copyright protection for purely AI-generated content\n- EU law to apply regardless of where AI was trained\n\n### 3. AI-Generated Content Code of Practice\nCommission published **second draft on 5 Mar 2026** — simplified and more flexible than first draft.\n\n### 4. AI Liability Directive — Withdrawn\nThe dedicated AILD was formally withdrawn Feb 2025. The **Product Liability Directive** (member states must transpose by **Dec 2026**) is now the primary legal mechanism for AI-related harm claims.\n\n### 5. Sectoral AI (Healthcare/Finance)\n- Medical AI: obligations apply Aug 2026; devices embedded in MDR/IVDR products get extension to Aug 2027\n- Finance: credit scoring classified as high-risk; full obligations Aug 2026\n- All member states need at least one **AI regulatory sandbox** operational by Aug 2026\n\n### 6. Apply AI Strategy & Competitiveness Push\n19 AI Factories underway across 16 member states; majority operational by end of 2026. Q2 2026 actions include calls for AI model sharing across Digital Innovation Hubs. The Apply AI Alliance coordinates industry/academia input.\n\n### 7. GPAI Implementing Act\nCommission consulting on draft enforcement rules for GPAI providers — specifying information requests, model recalls, and fines. GPAI enforcement begins Aug 2026.\n\n---\n\nSources:\n- [EU Council — Digital Omnibus (13 Mar 2026)](https://www.consilium.europa.eu/en/press/press-releases/2026/03/13/council-agrees-position-to-streamline-rules-on-artificial-intelligence/)\n- [EP — nudification ban vote](https://www.europarl.europa.eu/news/en/agenda/plenary-news/2026-03-25/2/artificial-intelligence-parliament-to-vote-on-nudification-ban)\n- [EP plenary March II 2026](https://epthinktank.eu/2026/03/24/european-parliament-plenary-session-march-ii-2026/)\n- [IAPP — MEPs reach preliminary agreement on AI omnibus](https://iapp.org/news/a/meps-reach-preliminary-political-agreement-on-AI-omnibus)\n- [CDT Europe AI Bulletin March 2026](https://cdt.org/insights/cdt-europes-ai-bulletin-march-2026/)\n- [Euronews — copyright resolution (10 Mar 2026)](https://www.euronews.com/next/2026/03/10/eu-parliament-urges-new-rules-to-protect-creative-works-from-ai-training)\n- [EP — copyright text adopted (TA-10-2026-0066)](https://www.europarl.europa.eu/doceo/document/TA-10-2026-0066_EN.html)\n- [IAPP — AI Liability Directive withdrawn](https://iapp.org/news/a/european-commission-withdraws-ai-liability-directive-from-consideration)\n- [The Regulatory Review — paradoxes of EU AI regulation (10 Mar 2026)](https://www.theregreview.org/2026/03/10/rangone-the-paradoxes-of-the-european-unions-ai-regulation/)\n- [EU Commission — Apply AI Strategy](https://digital-strategy.ec.europa.eu/en/policies/apply-ai)" ;
	<http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "[researcher] The file write requires your approval. Please approve the write to `/private/tmp" ;
	a <https://schema.org/EpisodicMemory> .


